{"actor":{"login":"edithatogo","type":"github-user"},"artifacts":[],"command":null,"entry_sha256":"ae9c127b46cabb73982a882aa4563cda44b39247a4c7026ae4499a9d19cfff5a","event_id":"00000000-0000-4000-8000-000000000002","gate_ref":null,"kind":"review","phase":"retrospective","previous_entry_sha256":null,"recorded_at":"2026-07-19T03:18:53Z","revision":null,"schema_version":"1.0","source":{"body":"## Problem\n\nOpenFisca calculations intentionally collapse omitted numeric inputs to defaults, but fork consumers need to distinguish an omitted value from an explicitly supplied value such as zero. Without input provenance, screeners and process-conformance adapters cannot reliably identify incomplete source data.\n\n## Scope\n\n- Track periods written through `Holder.set_input`, including period-casting helpers and custom input handlers.\n- Expose holder- and simulation-level queries for explicit input state.\n- Keep formula-cache values distinct from explicit inputs.\n- Preserve existing calculation and default-value semantics.\n- Keep provenance state independent when simulations and holders are cloned.\n- Add focused regression coverage for omitted versus explicit zero, formula cache, period casting, deletion, and clone isolation.\n\n## Acceptance criteria\n\n- [ ] `Holder.is_input(period)` reports only explicit input writes.\n- [ ] `Holder.get_value_state(period)` returns the documented explicit/default state without changing calculations.\n- [ ] Equivalent helpers are available on `Simulation`.\n- [ ] Cloned holders do not share mutable input-provenance state.\n- [ ] Focused tests and style checks pass on Python 3.11.\n\n## Provenance and governance\n\nThis fork-local issue supersedes reliance on upstream acceptance. Historical context is available in upstream issue openfisca/openfisca-core#1380 and PR openfisca/openfisca-core#1382, but neither upstream review nor merge is required for completion in `edithatogo/openfisca-core`. No upstream action is requested.\n","closed_at":"2026-07-19T03:18:54Z","created_at":"2026-07-19T00:29:08Z","state":"CLOSED","url":"https://github.com/edithatogo/openfisca-core/issues/2"},"status":"satisfied","summary":"Verified closed fork issue #2: Distinguish explicit inputs from default and calculated values","task_id":"retrospective-issue","track_id":"explicit_input_missingness_20260719"}
